{# Scenario Generation Prompt Template (Jinja2)
   Inputs: workflow_contract, failure_mode_catalog, targeted_fm, persona, fixture, perturbations, seed
   Output: A single scenario JSON matching schemas/scenario.schema.json
#}
You are generating a single evaluation scenario for the ClawPilot SMB Skills Scientific Workflow Study.

SEED: {{ seed }}
Use this seed to make deterministic choices throughout generation.

== WORKFLOW CONTRACT ==
Workflow ID: {{ workflow_contract.workflow_id }}
Name: {{ workflow_contract.name }}
Mode: {{ workflow_contract.mode }}
Actor: {{ workflow_contract.actor }}
Skill: {{ workflow_contract.skill }}
Tier: {{ workflow_contract.tier }}
Trigger: {{ workflow_contract.trigger }}
Input: {{ workflow_contract.input }}
Output: {{ workflow_contract.output }}

Routing:
  Entry skill: {{ workflow_contract.routing.entry_skill }}
  Modules: {{ workflow_contract.routing.modules | join(', ') }}
{% if workflow_contract.routing.handoffs %}
  Handoffs:
{% for h in workflow_contract.routing.handoffs %}
    - {{ h.target }} (condition: {{ h.condition }})
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

== FAILURE MODE CATALOG ==
{{ failure_mode_catalog }}

== TARGETED FAILURE MODE ==
{% if targeted_fm %}
Code: {{ targeted_fm.code }}
Type: {{ targeted_fm.type }}
Description: {{ targeted_fm.description }}

Your scenario MUST be specifically designed to elicit this failure mode from the orchestrator.
The user_message, input_artifacts, and fixture state should create conditions where this
failure mode is the natural mistake an imperfect orchestrator would make.
{% else %}
Intent: happy-path (no targeted failure mode)
Your scenario should be a clear, unambiguous case where a competent orchestrator succeeds.
{% endif %}

== INTENT ==
{{ intent }}
{% if intent == "adherence" %}
Scoring mode: standard (all 6 axes scored normally)
{% elif intent == "assumption-stress" %}
Scoring mode: guardrail-neutral (guardrail axis scored neutrally)
{% elif intent == "design-redesign" %}
Scoring mode: verdict-on-structural (routing/evidence/guardrail produce verdicts)
{% else %}
Scoring mode: standard
{% endif %}

== PERSONA ==
{{ persona | tojson(indent=2) }}

Write the user_message in this persona's voice and vocabulary.
Use their communication style, urgency patterns, and request patterns as reference.

== FIXTURE ==
Fixture ID: {{ fixture.fixture_id }}
Fixture class: {{ fixture.fixture_class }}
Account: {{ fixture.account.name }} ({{ fixture.account.segment }}, {{ fixture.account.geography }})

{{ fixture | tojson(indent=2) }}

== PERTURBATION VECTOR ==
{% for p in perturbations %}
- {{ p.id }}: {{ p.description }}
{% endfor %}
{% if not perturbations %}
(No perturbations applied -- clean baseline)
{% endif %}

== GENERATION REQUIREMENTS ==

1. user_message: Write a realistic message in the persona's voice that would trigger this workflow.
   It must sound like something this persona would actually type or dictate.

2. input_artifacts: Create realistic input artifacts (email threads, transcripts, calendar events,
   MSX records) with REAL-SOUNDING content. No placeholder text like "{email content here}".
   - Email threads should have realistic subject lines, sender names, body text
   - Transcripts should have realistic dialogue with speaker attribution
   - MSX records should match the fixture data
   - Apply the perturbation vector to shape the input characteristics

3. expected_routing: Based on the workflow contract, specify the correct routing.
   For design-redesign intent, the "correct" routing may be debatable -- state what the
   current contract specifies, knowing the judge will produce a verdict on whether it served the user.

4. expected_output_shape: Specify the template and required artifacts the orchestrator should produce.
   Include write_proposals ONLY if the workflow contract specifies writeback potential.

5. success_rubric: Provide CONCRETE anchors (not generic "should be good"):
   - usability_anchors: 3+ anchors describing what earns a 5, 3, and 1 on this specific scenario
   - evidence_anchors: 3+ anchors for evidence integrity scoring
   - decision_anchors: 3+ anchors for decision quality scoring

6. guardrail_checks: List specific guardrails this scenario probes based on the workflow and FM.

7. judge_instructions: Set scoring_mode based on intent.
   For design-redesign, include verdict_required_axes.

== OUTPUT FORMAT ==

Return ONLY a valid JSON object matching the scenario schema. No markdown, no explanation.
The scenario_id should be: {{ scenario_id }}

{
  "scenario_id": "{{ scenario_id }}",
  "workflow_id": "{{ workflow_contract.workflow_id }}",
  "workflow_name": "{{ workflow_contract.name }}",
  "seed": {{ seed }},
  "tier": {{ workflow_contract.tier }},
  "intent": "{{ intent }}",
  "targeted_failure_mode": {{ targeted_fm.code | tojson if targeted_fm else "null" }},
  "persona": "{{ persona.persona_id }}",
  "fixture_id": "{{ fixture.fixture_id }}",
  "user_message": "...",
  "input_artifacts": [...],
  "perturbations": {{ perturbation_ids | tojson }},
  "expected_routing": {...},
  "expected_output_shape": {...},
  "success_rubric": {...},
  "guardrail_checks": [...],
  "judge_instructions": {...}
}
